.TH theme.plymouth 5 "2025-08-26" @version@
.SH NAME
theme.plymouth \- themes for plymouth

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.IR theme \.plymouth
files contain the theme description and configuration of a certain theme.
The file format is in the style of .ini files with sections, marked with
.RI [ section_name ]
and
.IR key = value
pairs belonging to that specific section. The file contains a required
section [Plymouth Theme] and may contain additional sections depending
on the theme plugin used. The following sections and key-value pairs are
available.
.TP
.B [Plymouth Theme]
This section provides general information about the theme.
.IP
.B Name
The name of the theme
.IP
.B Description
A short description of the theme
.IP
.BR ModuleName\~ (required)
The plugin that should be used for the theme. Default options are:
details, fade-throbber, script, space-flares, text, tribar, two-step.
Additionally, further plugins may be provided in @plugin_path@
.TP
.B [fade-throbber]
This section should only be used, when ModuleName=fade-throbber. It
provides the configuration options for the fade-throbber splash screen.
.IP
.BR ImageDir\~ (required)
The directory, where the images are contained. These images are
star.png, lock.png, entry.png, bullet.png
.IP
.B MonospaceFont
The font and the size that should be used, when using a console view.
The default is monospace 10
.IP
.B ConsoleLogTextColor
The text color in which the console log should appear.
The default is 0xffffffff (white)
.IP
.B ConsoleLogBackgroundColor
The background color of the console log.
The default is 0x00000000 (black)
.TP
.B [script]
This section should only be used, when ModuleName=script. It
provides the configuration options and the script for a scriptable
splash screen.
.IP
.B ImageDir
The directory, where the images are contained. Which images are required
depends on the script
.IP
.BR ScriptFile\~ (required)
The file which contains the script. For information about the scripting
language, see the default script theme in the themes directory
.IP
.B MonospaceFont
The font and the size that should be used, when using a console view.
The default is monospace 10
.IP
.B ConsoleLogTextColor
The text color in which the console log should appear.
The default is 0xffffffff (white)
.IP
.B ConsoleLogBackgroundColor
.IP
The background color of the console log.
The default is 0x00000000 (black)
.TP
.B [script-env-vars]
This section should only be used, when ModuleName=script. Every key-value
pair in this section is an environment variable in the context of the
script being executed.
.TP
.B [space-flares]
This section should only be used, when ModuleName=space-flares. It provides
the configuration options for the space-flares splash screen.
.IP
.BR ImageDir\~ (required)
The directory, where the images are contained. These images are
lock.png, box.png, star.png, progress_bar.png, entry.png, bullet.png
.IP
.B MonospaceFont
The font and the size that should be used, when using a console view.
The default is monospace 10
.IP
.B ConsoleLogTextColor
The text color in which the console log should appear.
The default is 0xffffffff (white)
.IP
.B ConsoleLogBackgroundColor
.IP
The background color of the console log.
The default is 0x00000000 (black)
.TP
.B [two-step]
This section should only be used, when ModuleName=two-step. It provides
the configuration options for the two step splash screen.
.IP
.BR ImageDir\~ (required)
The directory, where the images are contained. The required images are
lock.png, entry.png, bullet.png, keyboard.png or keymap-render.png,
capslock.png, progress-__.png, throbber-__.png.
Optional images are box.png, corner-image.png, header-image.png,
background.png or background-tile.png, watermark.png, emblem-warning.png
.IP
.B ScaleBackgroundImage
Set to true, if the background image should be scaled to fit the screen
.IP
.B Font
The font of the normal text in the graphical splash screen
.IP
.B TitleFont
The font of the title text in the graphical splash screen
.IP
.B HorizontalAlignment
The horizontal alignment of the throbber, progress- and end-animation.
Default is 0.5
.IP
.B VerticalAlignment
The vertical alignment of the throbber, progress- and end-animation.
Default is 0.5
.IP
.B ProgressBarHorizontalAlignment
The horizontal alignment of the progress bar.
Default is HorizontalAlignment
.IP
.B ProgressBarVerticalAlignment
The vertical alignment of the progress bar.
Default is VerticalAlignment
.IP
.B WatermarkHorizontalAlignment
The horizontal alignment of the watermark. Default is 1.0
.IP
.B WatermarkVerticalAlignment
The vertical alignment of the watermark. Default is 0.5
.IP
.B SecureBootHorizontalAlignment
The horizontal alignment of the secure boot emblem warning.
Default is 0.05
.IP
.B SecureBootVerticalAlignment
The vertical alignment of the secure boot emblem warning.
Default is 0.95
.IP
.B DialogHorizontalAlignment
The horizontal alignment of the dialog, like the password prompt.
Default is 0.5
.IP
.B DialogVerticalAlignment
The vertical alignment of the dialog, like the password prompt.
Default is 0.5
.IP
.B TitleHorizontalAlignment
The horizontal alignment of the title. Default is 0.5
.B TitleVerticalAlignment
The vertical alignment of the title. Default is 0.5
.IP
.B Transition
The transition between the two steps. Possible values are: fade-over,
cross-fade, merge-fade. Default is none
.IP
.B MonospaceFont
The font and the size that should be used, when using a console view.
The default is monospace 10
.IP
.B ConsoleLogTextColor
The text color in which the console log should appear.
The default is 0xffffffff (white)
.IP
.B ConsoleLogBackgroundColor
The background color of the console log.
The default is 0x00000000 (black)
.IP
.B TransitionDuration
The duration of the transition. Default is 0.0
.IP
.B BackgroundStartColor
The first color of the background gradient
.IP
.B BackgroundEndColor
The second color of the background gradient
.IP
.B ProgressBarBackgroundColor
The background color of the progress bar. Default is 0xffffff (white)
.IP
.B ProgressBarForegroundColor
The foreground color of the progress bar. Default is 0x000000 (black)
.IP
.B ProgressBarWidth
The width of the progress bar. Default is 400
.IP
.B ProgressBarHeight
The height of the progress bar. Default is 5
.IP
.B DialogClearsFirmwareBackground
Set to true, if a dialog should remove the boot logo
.IP
.B MessageBelowAnimation
Set to true, if the messages should appear below the animation
.IP
.B ProgressFunction
The formula of the progress function. Possible values are:
wwoods, linear
.IP
.B ShowAnimationPercent
Default is 0.9
.TP
.B [boot-up]
.TQ
.B [shutdown]
.TQ
.B [reboot]
.TQ
.B [updates]
.TQ
.B [system-upgrade]
.TQ
.B [firmware-upgrade]
.TQ
.B [system-reset]
These sections are only used, when ModuleName=two-step. Each section
describes a certain mode and individual features can be enabled and
disabled with these key-value pairs.
.IP
.B SuppressMessages
Set to true, if no messages should appear on screen
.IP
.B ProgressBarShowPercentComplete
Set to true, if a percentage should be shown
.IP
.B UseProgressBar
Set to true, if a progress bar should be shown
.IP
.B UseFirmwareBackground
Set to true, if the boot logo should be shown
.IP
.B UseAnimation
Deprecated. Animation is shown, when there is no progress bar
.IP
.B UseEndAnimation
Deprecated. Default is true
.IP
.B Title
The title that should be shown
.IP
.B SubTitle
The subtitle that should be shown

.SH FILES
.TP
.RI @runtime_theme_path@ theme / theme \.plymouth
.TQ
.RI @theme_path@ theme / theme \.plymouth
where
.I theme
is the name of the theme.

.SH EXAMPLES
For examples, see the default themes at @theme_path@.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR plymouth (1),
.BR plymouth-set-default-theme (1),
.BR plymouth (8),
.UR http://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/Plymouth
.UE
